267
00:16:40.103 --> 00:16:41.931
Liar! You lied.

268
00:16:42.034 --> 00:16:43.655
You let people think I was lying.

269
00:16:43.758 --> 00:16:45.620
He really did love you.

270
00:16:49.344 --> 00:16:50.413
That was the truth of it.

271
00:16:56.448 --> 00:16:58.068
What was he like
when you married him?

272
00:16:59.206 --> 00:17:00.551
The same.

273
00:17:02.206 --> 00:17:03.206
Except...

274
00:17:03.724 --> 00:17:05.068
What?

275
00:17:05.655 --> 00:17:07.965
I was the apple of his eye.

276
00:17:10.000 --> 00:17:11.724
Then it... after a while.

277
00:17:11.827 --> 00:17:14.310
it was all. "Victoria. Victoria".

278
00:17:15.931 --> 00:17:17.931
But. you know...

279
00:17:20.517 --> 00:17:23.068
You had a lovely life. Victoria.

280
00:17:23.931 --> 00:17:25.689
Lovely school.

281
00:17:26.517 --> 00:17:28.068
Lovely room.

282
00:17:29.310 --> 00:17:31.586
Someone who loved you
and wanted to be close.

283
00:17:32.965 --> 00:17:36.517
All the opportunities of
a good education and career.

284
00:17:36.620 --> 00:17:38.000
Women of my generation.

285
00:17:38.103 --> 00:17:40.931
most of us ended up with our
heads in the washing machine.

286
00:17:46.724 --> 00:17:48.655
Why did you take Madeleine from me?

287
00:17:49.448 --> 00:17:50.724
Was Dad's idea.

288
00:17:51.344 --> 00:17:54.517
He wanted you to stay young and free.

289
00:17:55.586 --> 00:17:56.586
Free?

290
00:17:56.655 --> 00:17:57.862
Yes.

291
00:17:58.931 --> 00:18:02.586
Mum. I've had a horrible life.

292
00:18:02.689 --> 00:18:05.310
Boo-hoo.

293
00:18:05.413 --> 00:18:07.034
You stole my life.

294
00:18:08.275 --> 00:18:09.620
You stole my child.

295
00:18:09.724 --> 00:18:11.965
You stole my husband.

296
00:18:12.068 --> 00:18:13.517
He was raping me!

297
00:18:13.620 --> 00:18:15.413
Please. not this again.

298
00:18:15.517 --> 00:18:18.517
You really remind me of him sometimes.

299
00:18:32.689 --> 00:18:34.275
I want you to say sorry.

300
00:18:36.965 --> 00:18:38.103
To who?

301
00:18:38.206 --> 00:18:40.758
To me! To us!

302
00:18:44.103 --> 00:18:46.068
You needed help. Victoria.

303
00:18:46.172 --> 00:18:47.206
That. I do regret.

304
00:18:50.206 --> 00:18:54.344
Even you know that you were
often very. very unwell.

305
00:18:55.275 --> 00:18:56.862
That's when it started.

306
00:19:04.586 --> 00:19:07.413
Your childhood
and adolescence. Victoria.

307
00:19:07.517 --> 00:19:08.689
were what they were.

308
00:19:12.620 --> 00:19:13.724
A living hell?

309
00:19:15.275 --> 00:19:16.862
What happened to you as a child

310
00:19:16.965 --> 00:19:18.827
was not your fault.

311
00:19:19.896 --> 00:19:21.344
It's possible you have

312
00:19:21.448 --> 00:19:23.689
developed other personalities.

313
00:19:23.793 --> 00:19:26.275
or alters. as a way to cope.

314
00:19:27.344 --> 00:19:28.724
This condition is called.

315
00:19:28.827 --> 00:19:31.448
Dissociative Identity Disorder.

316
00:19:38.827 --> 00:19:41.793
I want us to build
compassion for each alter.

317
00:19:41.896 --> 00:19:43.517
but first. we have to meet them.

318
00:19:48.000 --> 00:19:49.000
I can try.

319
00:19:51.758 --> 00:19:52.758
No promises.

320
00:20:25.379 --> 00:20:27.689
It feels like you've accessed the alter

321
00:20:27.793 --> 00:20:30.379
that protects you in
the world by disengaging.

322
00:20:48.206 --> 00:20:49.482
Your inner child.

323
00:20:51.310 --> 00:20:55.000
A personality safe and unaware
of the trauma you've suffered.

324
00:20:58.931 --> 00:21:00.206
<i>Your father and I.</i>

325
00:21:00.310 --> 00:21:02.620
<i>we used to call you Victoria ragdoll.</i>

326
00:21:03.965 --> 00:21:06.965
<i>You were stuffed full of little
bits of other people.</i>

327
00:21:09.724 --> 00:21:12.620
<i>It really didn't matter
what happened to you.</i>

328
00:21:13.344 --> 00:21:15.172
<i>It's not just us. you know.</i>

329
00:21:15.275 --> 00:21:16.517
<i>We are many.</i>

330
00:21:18.241 --> 00:21:20.068
<i>Even Madeleine seemed like</i>

331
00:21:20.172 --> 00:21:23.344
<i>just another little Russian
ragdoll inside you.</i>

332
00:21:26.517 --> 00:21:28.172
<i>It's not just us. you know.</i>

333
00:21:33.310 --> 00:21:35.103
<i>My name is Legion.</i>

334
00:21:37.379 --> 00:21:38.931
<i>It's not just us.</i>

335
00:21:42.448 --> 00:21:44.793
Stop! Make it stop!

336
00:21:50.379 --> 00:21:51.689
No. I can't face that one.

337
00:21:53.103 --> 00:21:55.517
Maybe that one is not the same.

338
00:21:57.689 --> 00:21:58.896
Not human.

339
00:22:14.275 --> 00:22:16.000
I'm not like you. Mary.

340
00:22:16.793 --> 00:22:18.172
I'm another kind of mother.

341
00:24:27.551 --> 00:24:29.034
Mummy's here.

342
00:24:37.275 --> 00:24:39.275
You can sleep. my little one.

343
00:25:51.689 --> 00:25:54.551
Hey! Excuse me.

344
00:25:54.655 --> 00:25:56.379
Stop! Stop!

345
00:26:00.103 --> 00:26:01.206
Stop!

346
00:26:01.896 --> 00:26:03.586
You need permission to be here.

347
00:26:56.965 --> 00:26:58.413
<i>Morning. Jeanette.</i>

348
00:26:58.517 --> 00:26:59.586
<i>Where first today?</i>

349
00:27:00.413 --> 00:27:02.931
The church where
Bethan Pryce's body was found.

350
00:27:03.034 --> 00:27:04.310
<i>Well. your case. your funeral.</i>

351
00:27:04.413 --> 00:27:06.103
<i>So. the church is perfect. Let's go.</i>

352
00:27:06.862 --> 00:27:08.862
To... What? You're coming with me?

353
00:27:08.965 --> 00:27:10.517
<i>Correct.</i>

354
00:27:10.620 --> 00:27:11.724
<i>I'm outside.</i>

355
00:27:12.758 --> 00:27:14.310
- Right.
<i>- See you downstairs.</i>

356
00:27:14.413 --> 00:27:15.620
OK.

357
00:27:30.206 --> 00:27:31.448
Police?

358
00:27:31.551 --> 00:27:34.344
Yes. Yes. DCI Jeanette Kilburn.

359
00:27:34.931 --> 00:27:36.103
Just you. is it?

360
00:27:36.206 --> 00:27:39.034
No. Er. we won't be long.
It'll only be a few questions.

361
00:27:39.137 --> 00:27:40.977
I know you've already
spoken to our colleagues.

362
00:27:42.172 --> 00:27:43.172
- Morning.
- Morning.

363
00:27:43.241 --> 00:27:44.758
- Can we see the crypt?
- Er...

364
00:27:44.862 --> 00:27:46.172
- Now. please.
- Yes. of course.

365
00:27:57.896 --> 00:27:59.216
<i>How do you think she got in here?</i>

366
00:28:00.448 --> 00:28:01.907
Er. there was an archaeological study

367
00:28:01.931 --> 00:28:04.413
back in 2004.

368
00:28:04.517 --> 00:28:08.965
Might be somebody got
access to the tomb then.

369
00:28:09.482 --> 00:28:11.620
The church isn't always locked.

370
00:28:12.310 --> 00:28:14.620
Someone could just
carry her in. I suppose.

371
00:28:15.655 --> 00:28:17.931
Her parents. they're...
they're welcome here.

372
00:28:18.034 --> 00:28:19.517
If it would give them comfort.

373
00:28:19.620 --> 00:28:21.448
She was. er.
a looked-after young person.

374
00:28:22.724 --> 00:28:25.344
I'm sorry she wasn't looked after better.

375
00:28:26.344 --> 00:28:27.655
The study found that

376
00:28:27.758 --> 00:28:30.344
any relics of St Jordan were long gone.

377
00:28:30.896 --> 00:28:31.896
Right.

378
00:28:31.965 --> 00:28:33.689
We'll need records of the dig.

379
00:28:33.793 --> 00:28:35.655
Names of everyone that
had access to the site.

380
00:28:35.758 --> 00:28:37.655
- Can you provide?
- I can do my best.

381
00:28:37.758 --> 00:28:41.068
We've identified the body as
a girl called Bethan Pryce.

382
00:28:41.172 --> 00:28:43.137
She was a student at
Beecham College in 2004.

383
00:28:43.241 --> 00:28:44.793
Did you know her?

384
00:28:44.896 --> 00:28:48.482
I... I joined in 2007. I'm afraid.

385
00:28:49.103 --> 00:28:51.965
My predecessor.
he died a few years ago.

386
00:28:53.172 --> 00:28:54.241
Bethan...

387
00:28:55.517 --> 00:28:57.482
It's hard to think of her in there all alone.

388
00:29:01.206 --> 00:29:02.517
Hello. Verity Pound.

389
00:29:03.793 --> 00:29:06.827
Yeah. just bear with me.
Terrible reception.

390
00:29:09.758 --> 00:29:10.793
Are you a churchgoer?

391
00:29:12.068 --> 00:29:13.172
No.

392
00:29:14.413 --> 00:29:18.034
I always hope people
can walk into a church

393
00:29:18.137 --> 00:29:19.689
and find what they're looking for.

394
00:29:20.689 --> 00:29:22.275
God?

395
00:29:24.655 --> 00:29:26.103
The strength they need...

396
00:29:27.551 --> 00:29:29.448
to continue a difficult path.

397
00:29:40.586 --> 00:29:41.866
<i>Can I ask you about the painting</i>

398
00:29:41.965 --> 00:29:43.206
<i>I was looking at in there?</i>

399
00:29:43.310 --> 00:29:45.103
Mary Magdalene?

400
00:29:45.206 --> 00:29:48.172
We. er. we used to
have her right at the front.

401
00:29:49.034 --> 00:29:50.655
I was worried that it might make

402
00:29:50.758 --> 00:29:53.620
the girls feel ashamed. embarrassed.

403
00:29:55.586 --> 00:29:57.586
We're all made to feel ashamed of things

404
00:29:57.689 --> 00:30:00.758
that. to us. are just like breathing.

405
00:30:04.482 --> 00:30:05.827
Is that Beecham College?

406
00:30:05.931 --> 00:30:07.517
Yes. that's right. There's a bridleway.

407
00:30:07.620 --> 00:30:09.034
Not many horses on it these days.

408
00:30:09.137 --> 00:30:11.000
You can walk it. But in this weather.

409
00:30:11.103 --> 00:30:12.413
it'll be pretty hard going.

410
00:30:12.517 --> 00:30:14.689
I really should walk it.

411
00:30:15.827 --> 00:30:16.827
Understood.

412
00:30:16.896 --> 00:30:18.034
You can keep the umbrella.

413
00:30:18.137 --> 00:30:19.758
And. take care.

414
00:30:20.448 --> 00:30:22.000
Thank you.

415
00:30:22.103 --> 00:30:25.275
There must be something from
outside Sophia Craven's office.

416
00:30:25.379 --> 00:30:26.517
Fucking find it.

417
00:30:29.310 --> 00:30:30.527
I'm gonna go up to Beecham College.

418
00:30:30.551 --> 00:30:31.689
It's closer than I thought.

419
00:30:31.793 --> 00:30:32.896
Just to get some headspace.

420
00:30:33.000 --> 00:30:36.689
So. er. you take the car.
I'll make my own way back.

421
00:30:36.793 --> 00:30:38.517
- Yeah. good. Push!
- OK.

422
00:30:38.620 --> 00:30:41.103
Right. what about
CCTV on the day of the...

423
00:33:08.862 --> 00:33:10.482
- <i>Hello?</i>
- I'm up at Beecham college.

424
00:33:10.586 --> 00:33:11.896
Yeah. it's all locked up.

425
00:33:12.000 --> 00:33:14.000
Looks like they've already
sent everybody home.

426
00:33:14.620 --> 00:33:17.793
I'll try the children's home.

427
00:33:17.896 --> 00:33:20.016
see if I can get any more
information on Bethan Pryce.

428
00:33:20.413 --> 00:33:21.653
<i>I've just sent you a photograph</i>

429
00:33:21.689 --> 00:33:23.551
of some. er. graffiti.

430
00:33:23.655 --> 00:33:24.931
OK. I've got it here.

431
00:33:25.034 --> 00:33:27.793
<i>I think this could be a clue from Victoria.</i>

432
00:33:27.896 --> 00:33:29.586
<i>Look it up. what it means.</i>

433
00:33:29.689 --> 00:33:31.137
OK. "Alma Mater".

434
00:33:31.241 --> 00:33:32.862
Literally means nourishing mother.

435
00:33:32.965 --> 00:33:34.862
Used to describe what uni.

436
00:33:34.965 --> 00:33:36.320
school or place of education you went to.

437
00:33:36.344 --> 00:33:37.931
<i>I don't usually get</i>

438
00:33:38.034 --> 00:33:39.965
the creeps. Mike. but. er...

439
00:33:41.275 --> 00:33:43.379
this is a funny fucking creepy place

440
00:33:43.482 --> 00:33:44.769
to send your kids for 30 grand a year.

441
00:33:44.793 --> 00:33:46.113
<i>Anyway. I'm off to Ledford House.</i>

442
00:33:46.206 --> 00:33:47.241
<i>the children's home.</i>

443
00:33:47.344 --> 00:33:48.620
<i>You chase up those tox reports.</i>

444
00:33:48.724 --> 00:33:49.758
All right. on it.

445
00:34:06.310 --> 00:34:07.689
I found Bethan's file.

446
00:34:08.620 --> 00:34:10.275
It says she was one of Beecham's

447
00:34:10.379 --> 00:34:11.965
charitable bursary recipients.

448
00:34:12.068 --> 00:34:15.103
Er. apparently. she was really bright.

449
00:34:15.206 --> 00:34:17.724
and then she was suspended
for non-attendance

450
00:34:18.241 --> 00:34:20.793
and listed by us as a runaway
around the same time.

451
00:34:20.896 --> 00:34:23.310
They say she ran away dozens
of times before then. too.

452
00:34:23.862 --> 00:34:26.137
You know. social services
might have more on the family.

453
00:34:27.379 --> 00:34:29.689
Children's home was
her guardian at the time.

454
00:34:30.586 --> 00:34:32.241
By way of a partnership agreement

455
00:34:32.344 --> 00:34:33.448
with a local authority.

456
00:34:35.620 --> 00:34:36.827
But. yes.

457
00:34:36.931 --> 00:34:38.034
All right.

458
00:34:39.448 --> 00:34:41.000
Did she leave anything behind?

459
00:34:41.103 --> 00:34:42.148
They often leave everything.

460
00:34:42.172 --> 00:34:43.827
They don't consider it their real stuff.

461
00:34:43.931 --> 00:34:45.331
It's just stuff they've been given.

462
00:34:45.793 --> 00:34:48.000
I know it's a long shot.
but did you keep any of it?

463
00:34:49.068 --> 00:34:50.344
No. Sorry.

464
00:34:50.965 --> 00:34:52.655
We'd have so much stuff if we did that.

465
00:34:52.758 --> 00:34:54.551
Yeah. OK.

466
00:34:55.137 --> 00:34:57.551
Er. it sounds like Bethan ran away a lot.

467
00:34:58.655 --> 00:34:59.976
There's not much we can do
when that happens.

468
00:35:00.000 --> 00:35:01.689
It's basically heartbreaking.

469
00:35:02.448 --> 00:35:03.620
Any idea where she went?

470
00:35:04.862 --> 00:35:06.137
It's not in her notes.

471
00:35:10.724 --> 00:35:11.827
Can I have a look around?

472
00:35:15.793 --> 00:35:16.896
What about you?

473
00:35:17.000 --> 00:35:18.000
Can you show me around?

474
00:35:18.103 --> 00:35:19.310
Hi.

475
00:35:19.413 --> 00:35:21.655
This is Lily.

476
00:35:21.758 --> 00:35:23.482
She's been here about six weeks.

477
00:35:23.586 --> 00:35:25.413
Doing really well. actually. Aren't you?

478
00:35:25.517 --> 00:35:27.551
Are you looking for your child?

479
00:35:28.241 --> 00:35:30.344
Me? No. No. I know where my boy is.

480
00:35:30.448 --> 00:35:31.689
He's with his dad.

481
00:35:31.793 --> 00:35:33.896
It's. er. it's nice to meet you.

482
00:35:34.000 --> 00:35:35.000
My name is Jeanette.

483
00:35:35.103 --> 00:35:36.344
I'm a police detective.

484
00:35:37.275 --> 00:35:38.517
A girl went missing. and...

485
00:35:38.620 --> 00:35:39.793
That was a long time ago.

486
00:35:39.896 --> 00:35:41.517
but. I'm just trying to find out

487
00:35:41.620 --> 00:35:42.793
a bit more about her.

488
00:35:43.482 --> 00:35:44.724
My room is this way.

489
00:35:45.896 --> 00:35:47.034
Can I take a look?

490
00:35:47.137 --> 00:35:48.137
Keep the door open.

491
00:35:49.344 --> 00:35:51.241
Yeah. that's fine. Thank you for checkin'.

492
00:35:51.862 --> 00:35:53.896
All right. Show me the way.

493
00:35:54.000 --> 00:35:55.862
It's just up here.

494
00:36:06.344 --> 00:36:08.862
This your bed?

495
00:36:09.551 --> 00:36:10.655
Yeah.

496
00:36:11.482 --> 00:36:12.724
Is that your own duvet cover?

497
00:36:13.310 --> 00:36:15.000
No. Belongs here.

498
00:36:16.310 --> 00:36:17.758
Your teddy?

499
00:36:17.862 --> 00:36:19.379
No. it's theirs.

500
00:36:20.000 --> 00:36:21.862
I didn't want to tell them I'm a bit old.

501
00:36:25.965 --> 00:36:27.482
Everything OK here?

502
00:36:27.586 --> 00:36:28.793
Everyone nice to you?

503
00:36:29.724 --> 00:36:30.931
Er... yeah.

504
00:36:34.620 --> 00:36:37.344
Some of the others have
a speaker or stereo.

505
00:36:37.448 --> 00:36:38.848
something like that in their rooms.

506
00:36:40.758 --> 00:36:41.758
Yeah?

507
00:36:41.827 --> 00:36:42.862
Yeah.

508
00:36:44.689 --> 00:36:45.758
I wanted to share a room.

509
00:36:45.862 --> 00:36:47.827
but they said I have to have
this one on my own.

510
00:36:53.931 --> 00:36:55.068
And why is that. then?

511
00:36:56.310 --> 00:36:58.344
They just said it makes it easier.

512
00:37:04.206 --> 00:37:05.310
Lily...

513
00:37:10.586 --> 00:37:12.931
I want to ask you if anything
weird happens here.

514
00:37:14.206 --> 00:37:15.344
Like what?

515
00:37:15.448 --> 00:37:16.517
I don't know.

516
00:37:17.655 --> 00:37:19.862
People hanging around?

517
00:37:19.965 --> 00:37:21.206
People you don't know.

518
00:37:22.172 --> 00:37:23.689
Men. Older men.

519
00:37:24.482 --> 00:37:26.793
I haven't seen any. Why?

520
00:37:26.896 --> 00:37:27.931
No. that's good.

521
00:37:37.724 --> 00:37:39.517
- Thanks again. Jackie.
- No problem.

522
00:37:39.620 --> 00:37:42.068
And I'll be in touch if
there's anything more. er...

523
00:37:42.172 --> 00:37:43.448
Hey. listen.

524
00:37:43.551 --> 00:37:45.000
Just so you know.

525
00:37:45.827 --> 00:37:47.448
she doesn't want that teddy bear.

526
00:37:47.551 --> 00:37:48.724
Right.

527
00:37:48.827 --> 00:37:50.707
Couldn't get her her own
duvet cover. could you?

528
00:37:53.310 --> 00:37:54.517
OK.

529
00:37:56.068 --> 00:37:57.758
Everyone always has a reaction.

530
00:37:57.862 --> 00:37:59.172
After a visit.

531
00:37:59.275 --> 00:38:00.310
Especially the mums.

532
00:38:01.103 --> 00:38:02.103
What do you mean by that?

533
00:38:03.000 --> 00:38:04.379
Everyone wants to save someone.

534
